{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2134,"text":"When I was a kid,"},{"time":3317,"text":"I experienced something so powerful,"},{"time":5849,"text":"I spent the rest of my life\nsearching for it,"},{"time":8947,"text":"and in all the wrong places."},{"time":11327,"text":"What I experienced wasn't virtual reality."},{"time":14633,"text":"It was music."},{"time":16251,"text":"And this is where the story begins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19797,"text":"That's me,"},{"time":21191,"text":"listening to the Beatles' \"White Album.\""},{"time":23161,"text":"And the look on my face is the feeling"},{"time":26353,"text":"that I've been searching for ever since."},{"time":29938,"text":"Music goes straight to the emotional vein,"},{"time":32548,"text":"into your bloodstream"},{"time":34178,"text":"and right into your heart."},{"time":36157,"text":"It deepens every experience."},{"time":39717,"text":"Fellas?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41454,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47472,"text":"This is the amazing McKenzie Stubbert"},{"time":49648,"text":"and Joshua Roman."},{"time":51551,"text":"Music --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52738,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53956,"text":"Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56630,"text":"Music makes everything\nhave more emotional resonance."},{"time":61229,"text":"Let's see how it does for this talk."},{"time":63825,"text":"The right piece of music\nat the right time fuses with us"},{"time":67593,"text":"on a cellular level."},{"time":69382,"text":"When I hear that one song"},{"time":72502,"text":"from that one summer"},{"time":74488,"text":"with that one girl,"},{"time":76480,"text":"I'm instantly transported\nback there again."},{"time":79963,"text":"Hey, Stacey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82908,"text":"Here's a part of the story, though,\nwhere I got a little greedy."},{"time":86210,"text":"I thought if I added more layers\non top of the music,"},{"time":90394,"text":"I could make the feelings\neven more powerful."},{"time":93670,"text":"So I got into directing music videos."},{"time":97432,"text":"This is what they looked like."},{"time":102429,"text":"That's my brother, Jeff."},{"time":104799,"text":"Sorry about this, Jeff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106145,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":107256,"text":"Here's me, just so we're even."},{"time":110682,"text":"Incredible moves."},{"time":112444,"text":"Should've been a dancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113809,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114955,"text":"These experiments grew,"},{"time":116291,"text":"and in time, started\nto look more like this."},{"time":121852,"text":"In both, I'm searching\nfor the same thing, though,"},{"time":124516,"text":"to capture that lightning in a bottle."},{"time":128192,"text":"Except, I'm not."},{"time":129889,"text":"Adding moving pictures over the music\nadded narrative dimension, yes,"},{"time":134261,"text":"but never quite equated the power"},{"time":136809,"text":"that just raw music had for me on its own."},{"time":140795,"text":"This is not a great thing to realize\nwhen you've devoted your life"},{"time":143973,"text":"and professional career\nto becoming a music video director."},{"time":146836,"text":"I kept asking myself,\ndid I take the wrong path?"},{"time":150353,"text":"So I started thinking: if I could\ninvolve you, the audience, more,"},{"time":154228,"text":"I might be able to make you\nfeel something more as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157901,"text":"So Aaron Koblin and I began\nauditioning new technologies"},{"time":161110,"text":"that could put more of you\ninside of the work,"},{"time":164272,"text":"like your childhood home\nin \"The Wilderness Downtown,\""},{"time":168750,"text":"your hand-drawn portraits,\nin \"The Johnny Cash Project,\""},{"time":173581,"text":"and your interactive dreams"},{"time":175791,"text":"in \"3 Dreams of Black.\""},{"time":179469,"text":"We were pushing beyond the screen,"},{"time":181450,"text":"trying to connect more deeply"},{"time":183455,"text":"to people's hearts and imaginations."},{"time":186745,"text":"But it wasn't quite enough."},{"time":189258,"text":"It still didn't have the raw\nexperiential power of pure music for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195443,"text":"So I started chasing a new technology"},{"time":197528,"text":"that I only had read about\nin science fiction."},{"time":200826,"text":"And after years of searching,\nI found a prototype."},{"time":203871,"text":"It was a project from Nonny de la Peña\nin Mark Bolas's lab in USC."},{"time":209102,"text":"And when I tried it, I knew I'd found it."},{"time":213095,"text":"I could taste the lightning."},{"time":215334,"text":"It was called virtual reality."},{"time":218047,"text":"This was it five years ago\nwhen I ran into it."},{"time":221530,"text":"This is what it looks like now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224846,"text":"I quickly started building things\nin this new medium,"},{"time":228775,"text":"and through that process\nwe realized something:"},{"time":231664,"text":"that VR is going to play\nan incredibly important role"},{"time":235105,"text":"in the history of mediums."},{"time":237681,"text":"In fact, it's going to be the last one."},{"time":241390,"text":"I mean this because it's the first medium\nthat actually makes the jump"},{"time":245029,"text":"from our internalization\nof an author's expression"},{"time":248341,"text":"of an experience,"},{"time":250035,"text":"to our experiencing it firsthand."},{"time":253691,"text":"You look confused.\nI'll explain. Don't worry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255879,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257830,"text":"If we go back to the origins of mediums,"},{"time":261044,"text":"by all best guesses,"},{"time":262432,"text":"it starts around a fire,\nwith a good story."},{"time":265986,"text":"Our clan leader is telling us"},{"time":267475,"text":"about how he hunted the woolly mammoth\non the tundra that day."},{"time":272069,"text":"We hear his words"},{"time":274090,"text":"and translate them\ninto our own internal truths."},{"time":278839,"text":"The same thing happens"},{"time":280028,"text":"when we look at the cave painting\nversion of the story,"},{"time":284241,"text":"the book about the mammoth hunt,"},{"time":286472,"text":"the play,"},{"time":288109,"text":"the radio broadcast,"},{"time":289749,"text":"the television show"},{"time":291582,"text":"or the movie."},{"time":293532,"text":"All of these mediums require\nwhat we call \"suspension of disbelief,\""},{"time":297288,"text":"because there's a translation gap\nbetween the reality of the story"},{"time":301370,"text":"and our consciousness\ninterpreting the story"},{"time":304816,"text":"into our reality."},{"time":307081,"text":"I'm using the word \"consciousness\"\nas a feeling of reality that we get"},{"time":311181,"text":"from our senses experiencing\nthe world around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316580,"text":"Virtual reality bridges that gap."},{"time":319985,"text":"Now, you are on the tundra\nhunting with the clan leader."},{"time":324222,"text":"Or you are the clan leader."},{"time":326600,"text":"Or maybe you're even the woolly mammoth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329326,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":334218,"text":"So here's what special about VR."},{"time":336726,"text":"In all other mediums,"},{"time":338329,"text":"your consciousness interprets the medium."},{"time":341044,"text":"In VR, your consciousness is the medium."},{"time":346399,"text":"So the potential for VR is enormous."},{"time":348857,"text":"But where are we now?"},{"time":350555,"text":"What is the current state of the art?"},{"time":354318,"text":"Well,"},{"time":356746,"text":"we are here."},{"time":358724,"text":"We are the equivalent\nof year one of cinema."},{"time":361896,"text":"This is the Lumière Brothers film"},{"time":363546,"text":"that allegedly sent a theater full\nof people running for their lives"},{"time":366929,"text":"as they thought a train\nwas coming toward them."},{"time":370136,"text":"Similar to this early stage\nof this medium,"},{"time":373436,"text":"in VR, we also have to move\npast the spectacle"},{"time":377001,"text":"and into the storytelling."},{"time":378911,"text":"It took this medium decades"},{"time":380682,"text":"to figure out its preferred\nlanguage of storytelling,"},{"time":383364,"text":"in the form of a feature film."},{"time":385164,"text":"In VR today, we're more learning grammar"},{"time":388542,"text":"than writing language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390880,"text":"We've made 15 films in the last year\nat our VR company, Vrse,"},{"time":394455,"text":"and we've learned a few things."},{"time":396801,"text":"We found that we have a unique,\ndirect path into your senses,"},{"time":400140,"text":"your emotions, even your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403897,"text":"So let me show you some things."},{"time":405596,"text":"For the purpose of this demo,"},{"time":407018,"text":"we're going to take every direction\nthat you could possibly look,"},{"time":410107,"text":"and stretch it into this giant rectangle."},{"time":413083,"text":"OK, here we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417642,"text":"So, first: camera movement\nis tricky in VR."},{"time":421947,"text":"Done wrong, it can actually make you sick."},{"time":424930,"text":"We found if you move the camera\nat a constant speed in a straight line,"},{"time":429453,"text":"you can actually get away with it, though."},{"time":431694,"text":"The first day in film school,"},{"time":433445,"text":"they told me you have to learn\nevery single rule"},{"time":436056,"text":"before you can break one."},{"time":437838,"text":"We have not learned every single rule."},{"time":440036,"text":"We've barely learned any at all,"},{"time":441588,"text":"but we're already trying to break them"},{"time":443429,"text":"to see what kind of creative things\nwe can accomplish."},{"time":445982,"text":"In this shot here, where we're moving up\noff the ground, I added acceleration."},{"time":449718,"text":"I did that because I wanted\nto give you a physical sensation"},{"time":452575,"text":"of moving up off the ground."},{"time":453982,"text":"In VR, I can give that to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457797,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463882,"text":"Not surprisingly, music matters a lot\nin this medium as well."},{"time":467842,"text":"It guides us how to feel."},{"time":470354,"text":"In this project we made\nwith the New York Times, Zach Richter"},{"time":473699,"text":"and our friend, JR,"},{"time":475478,"text":"we take you up in a helicopter,"},{"time":477387,"text":"and even though you're flying\n2,000 feet above Manhattan,"},{"time":481349,"text":"you don't feel afraid."},{"time":482961,"text":"You feel triumphant for JR's character."},{"time":487022,"text":"The music guides you there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488525,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":497364,"text":"Contrary to popular belief,"},{"time":498995,"text":"there is composition in virtual reality,"},{"time":501685,"text":"but it's completely\ndifferent than in film,"},{"time":503770,"text":"where you have a rectangular frame."},{"time":505519,"text":"Composition is now\nwhere your consciousness exists"},{"time":508055,"text":"and how the world moves around you."},{"time":510927,"text":"In this film, \"Waves of Grace,\"\nwhich was a collaboration between Vrse,"},{"time":514315,"text":"the United Nations, Gabo Arora,\nand Imraan Ismail,"},{"time":517248,"text":"we also see the changing role\nof the close-up in virtual reality."},{"time":521139,"text":"A close-up in VR means\nyou're actually close up to someone."},{"time":525954,"text":"It brings that character inside\nof your personal space,"},{"time":528621,"text":"a space that we'd usually reserve\nfor the people that we love."},{"time":532490,"text":"And you feel an emotional\ncloseness to the character"},{"time":535684,"text":"because of what you feel\nto be a physical closeness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544639,"text":"Directing VR is not like\ndirecting for the rectangle."},{"time":549002,"text":"It's more of a choreography\nof the viewer's attention."},{"time":552864,"text":"One tool we can use\nto guide your attention"},{"time":555482,"text":"is called \"spatialized sound.\""},{"time":556939,"text":"I can put a sound anywhere\nin front of you, to left or right,"},{"time":559931,"text":"even behind you,"},{"time":561334,"text":"and when you turn your head,\nthe sound will rotate accordingly."},{"time":564354,"text":"So I can use that to direct your attention\nto where I want you to see."},{"time":568308,"text":"Next time you hear someone\nsinging over your shoulder,"},{"time":570910,"text":"it might be Bono."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572195,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578539,"text":"VR makes us feel\nlike we are part of something."},{"time":582459,"text":"For most of human history,\nwe lived in small family units."},{"time":585992,"text":"We started in caves,"},{"time":587527,"text":"then moved to clans and tribes,\nthen villages and towns,"},{"time":590984,"text":"and now we're all global citizens."},{"time":594211,"text":"But I believe that we are still\nhardwired to care the most"},{"time":598035,"text":"about the things that are local to us."},{"time":601325,"text":"And VR makes anywhere\nand anyone feel local."},{"time":606307,"text":"That's why it works as an empathy machine."},{"time":608839,"text":"Our film \"Clouds Over Sidra\"\ntakes you to a Syrian refugee camp,"},{"time":612087,"text":"and instead of watching a story\nabout people over there,"},{"time":616662,"text":"it's now a story about us here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622386,"text":"But where do we go from here?"},{"time":624432,"text":"The tricky thing is that\nwith all previous mediums,"},{"time":626913,"text":"the format is fixed at its birth."},{"time":630182,"text":"Film has been a sequence of rectangles,"},{"time":632095,"text":"from Muybridge and his horses to now."},{"time":635377,"text":"The format has never changed."},{"time":637654,"text":"But VR as a format, as a medium,"},{"time":642370,"text":"isn't complete yet."},{"time":644767,"text":"It's not using physical celluloid\nor paper or TV signals."},{"time":647990,"text":"It actually employs what we use\nto make sense of the world."},{"time":652642,"text":"We're using your senses\nas the paints on the canvas,"},{"time":656569,"text":"but only two right now."},{"time":659653,"text":"Eventually, we can see if we will have\nall of our human senses employed,"},{"time":663517,"text":"and we will have agency to live\nthe story in any path we choose."},{"time":668575,"text":"And we call it virtual reality right now,"},{"time":671055,"text":"but what happens when we move\npast simulated realities?"},{"time":675345,"text":"What do we call it then?"},{"time":677503,"text":"What if instead of verbally\ntelling you about a dream,"},{"time":680363,"text":"I could let you live inside that dream?"},{"time":683860,"text":"What if instead of just experiencing\nvisiting some reality on Earth,"},{"time":687511,"text":"you could surf gravitational waves\non the edge of a black hole,"},{"time":691961,"text":"or create galaxies from scratch,"},{"time":694761,"text":"or communicate with each other\nnot using words"},{"time":697869,"text":"but using our raw thoughts?"},{"time":701254,"text":"That's not a virtual reality anymore."},{"time":704052,"text":"And honestly I don't know\nwhat that's called."},{"time":706884,"text":"But I hope you see where we're going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710629,"text":"But here I am, intellectualizing\na medium I'm saying is experiential."},{"time":714839,"text":"So let's experience it."},{"time":716845,"text":"In your hands, you hopefully hold\na piece of cardboard."},{"time":721143,"text":"Let's open the flap."},{"time":722800,"text":"Tap on the power button\nto unlock the phone."},{"time":726145,"text":"For the people watching at home,"},{"time":727793,"text":"we're going to put up a card right now"},{"time":729653,"text":"to show you how to download\nthis experience on your phone yourself,"},{"time":732907,"text":"and even get a Google cardboard\nof your own to try it with."},{"time":737275,"text":"We played in cardboard boxes as kids,"},{"time":739826,"text":"and as adults, I'm hoping we can all find\na little bit of that lightning"},{"time":744434,"text":"by sticking our head in one again."},{"time":749615,"text":"You're about to participate"},{"time":751068,"text":"in the largest collective\nVR viewing in history."},{"time":756236,"text":"And in that classic old-timey\nstyle of yesteryear,"},{"time":759878,"text":"we're all going to watch something"},{"time":762133,"text":"at the exact same time, together."},{"time":765019,"text":"Let's hope it works."},{"time":766466,"text":"What's the countdown\nlook like? I can't see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772564,"text":"Audience: ...15, 14, 13, 12, 11, 10, 9,"},{"time":779582,"text":"8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1"}]},{"cues":[{"time":790327,"text":"(Birds singing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":802508,"text":"(Train engine)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":813351,"text":"Audience: (Shreiks)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":831285,"text":"(Video) JR: Let me tell you"},{"time":832599,"text":"how I shot the cover\nof the New York Times Magazine,"},{"time":835100,"text":"\"Walking New York.\""},{"time":846577,"text":"I just got strapped on\noutside the helicopter,"},{"time":850011,"text":"and I had to be perfectly\nvertical so I could grab it."},{"time":854279,"text":"And when I was perfectly above --"},{"time":855921,"text":"you know, with the wind,\nwe had to redo it a few times --"},{"time":858682,"text":"then I kept shooting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867598,"text":"(Video) Woman's voice: Dear Lord,"},{"time":869900,"text":"protect us from evil,"},{"time":872654,"text":"for you are the Lord,"},{"time":875044,"text":"the light."},{"time":881824,"text":"You who gave us life took it away."},{"time":886191,"text":"Let your will be done."},{"time":888941,"text":"Please bring peace to the many\nwho have lost loved ones."},{"time":893529,"text":"Help us to live again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898564,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":917066,"text":"(Video) (Children's voices)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":919504,"text":"Child's voice: There are more kids\nin Zaatari than adults right now."},{"time":929924,"text":"Sometimes I think"},{"time":931977,"text":"we are the ones in charge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939410,"text":"Chris Milk: How was it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":940809,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":944548,"text":"That was a cheap way of getting you\nto do a standing ovation."},{"time":947501,"text":"I just made you all stand.\nI knew you'd applaud at the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950333,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":951998,"text":"I believe that everyone on Earth\nneeds to experience"},{"time":955841,"text":"what you just experienced."},{"time":958036,"text":"That way we can collectively\nstart to shape this,"},{"time":961227,"text":"not as a tech platform"},{"time":963025,"text":"but as a humanity platform."},{"time":965498,"text":"And to that end, in November of last year,"},{"time":968706,"text":"the New York Times and Vrse made\na VR project called \"The Displaced.\""},{"time":972016,"text":"It launched with one million\nGoogle Cardboards"},{"time":974386,"text":"sent out to every Sunday subscriber\nwith their newspaper."},{"time":977883,"text":"But a funny thing happened\nthat Sunday morning."},{"time":980425,"text":"A lot of people got them"},{"time":981771,"text":"that were not the intended recipients\non the mailing label."},{"time":986001,"text":"And we started seeing this\nall over Instagram."},{"time":993059,"text":"Look familiar?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":996252,"text":"Music led me on a path"},{"time":998419,"text":"of searching for what seemed\nlike the unattainable"},{"time":1001492,"text":"for a very long time."},{"time":1003466,"text":"Now, millions of kids just had\nthe same formative experience"},{"time":1007461,"text":"in their childhood"},{"time":1009226,"text":"that I had in mine."},{"time":1012316,"text":"Only I think this one"},{"time":1014569,"text":"surpasses it."},{"time":1016358,"text":"Let's see"},{"time":1017859,"text":"where this"},{"time":1019573,"text":"leads them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021384,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022559,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}